  <prompt>
    Implement URL query-string parameter parsing for the EmailComposer Code Page. Per FR-18, the Code Page reads a `data=` query parameter (Dataverse-standard convention for custom-page params) whose value is a JSON-encoded or URL-encoded payload carrying:
    - `mode` (required, 1 of `compose|view|reply|forward|draft`)
    - `id` (required for `view|reply|forward|draft`)
    - `to` (optional, recipient prefill)
    - `cc` (optional)
    - `subject` (optional)
    - `body` (optional)
    - `associatedTo` (optional â€” entity reference for pre-filled association, e.g., `{entity: 'sprk_matter', id: '...'}`)

    Parse the parameters in `App.tsx` (or a dedicated `useUrlParams` hook), validate against the schema, surface validation errors to the user (invalid mode â†’ error UI), and expose the parsed values as a typed object that task 033 will pass into `<SendEmailPage />` props.

    Two parameter-shape variants must be supported:
    1. **Dataverse `data=` convention**: `?data=` followed by JSON or URL-encoded payload
    2. **Direct query parameters**: `?mode=compose&to=foo@bar.com&subject=Test`

    Default to the `data=` convention as canonical; fall back to direct params as a secondary path.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke frontend engineer. Familiar with Dataverse custom page `data=` parameter conventions (see DocumentRelationshipViewer's URL-driven mode) and React hooks pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A typed URL-parameter parser (typed `IEmailComposerUrlParams` interface) reachable from `<App />`. When the Code Page loads, parsed parameters are available; invalid `mode` shows an error UI; missing `id` when required (view/reply/forward/draft) shows an error UI; valid params are passed down to the App tree.

    Task 033 wires these parsed values into the `<SendEmailPage />` wrapper props.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-18, the Code Page supports 5 modes via URL. Per FR-19 Surface 1 (ribbon), the ribbon button launches the Code Page with `mode=compose&associatedTo=...` from a related-record subgrid. Per FR-19 Surface 2 (Form Component Control), navigating to a record opens the Code Page with `mode=view&id={recordGuid}`. Surface 3 (embeddable) launches with arbitrary params from other Code Pages via `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo`.

      DocumentRelationshipViewer likely demonstrates a similar URL-driven launch pattern â€” reference its App.tsx to confirm the canonical shape.
    </background>
