  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read FR-18 in spec + FR-19 (entry surfaces) to confirm exact param semantics.</step>
    <step order="2">Read DocumentRelationshipViewer's `App.tsx` to see how it handles URL params (Dataverse `data=` convention or direct).</step>
    <step order="3">Create `src/types/url.ts` defining `IEmailComposerUrlParams` interface: `{ mode: 'compose'|'view'|'reply'|'forward'|'draft', id?: string, to?: string, cc?: string, subject?: string, body?: string, associatedTo?: { entity: string, id: string } }`.</step>
    <step order="4">Create `src/hooks/useUrlParams.ts` exporting `useUrlParams(): { params: IEmailComposerUrlParams | null, error: string | null }`. Logic: read `window.location.search`, try `data=` first (parse + URL-decode), fall back to direct params; validate; return typed object or error.</step>
    <step order="5">Add validation: if `mode` not in allowed set â†’ error "Invalid mode: {value}"; if `mode` requires `id` and `id` missing â†’ error "Missing required `id` for mode {mode}".</step>
    <step order="6">Update `src/App.tsx` â€” call `useUrlParams()`; if error, render Fluent v9 `<MessageBar>` error UI; if valid, store params in state for downstream consumers (task 033 wires into wrapper props).</step>
    <step order="7">Write minimal Vitest/Jest unit tests for `useUrlParams` if test infra is wired in the Code Page scaffold; otherwise document parsing examples as JSDoc on the hook.</step>
    <step order="8">Run `npm run build`; confirm clean build, no TypeScript errors.</step>
    <step order="9">Manual smoke: open the Code Page with a few URL variants (e.g., `?data=%7B%22mode%22%3A%22compose%22%7D`, `?mode=view&id=abc`, `?mode=invalid`) and confirm parsing/error behavior.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 032 âś… completed.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status â†’ completed; advance to next pending task (033).</step>
  </steps>

